<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<title>Parts Example - Basil</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="/public/styles.css"/>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="container">
		<h1>Parts Example</h1>
		<p>This demonstrates interactive Parts with multiple view functions.</p>
		
		<div class="demo">
			<h2>Counter Part</h2>
			<p>Click the buttons to increment, decrement, or reset the counter.</p>
			<p>Notice how the count updates without a full page reload!</p>
			
			<div class="part-container">
				<Part src={@./counter.part} view="default" count={0}/>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<div class="info">
			<h2>How it Works</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Part Attributes:</strong> <code>part-click</code> defines which view to call on click</li>
				<li><strong>Props:</strong> The <code>part-count</code> attribute passes the current count</li>
				<li><strong>Form Submit:</strong> <code>part-submit</code> handles form submissions</li>
				<li><strong>Loading States:</strong> The <code>.part-loading</code> class is added during updates</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		
		<div class="code-example">
			<h2>Code Example</h2>
			<pre><code>{`// counter.part
export default = fn(props) {
  let count = props.count
  <div>
    <p>Count: {count}</p>
    <button part-click="increment" part-count={count}>+</button>
    <button part-click="decrement" part-count={count}>-</button>
  </div>
}

export increment = fn(props) {
  let newCount = props.count + 1
  <div>
    <p>Count: {newCount}</p>
    <button part-click="increment" part-count={newCount}>+</button>
    <button part-click="decrement" part-count={newCount}>-</button>
  </div>
}`}</code></pre>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>
